  <description type="morphology">Leaves mostly in 3s, often recurved, linear to lanceolate, 4--15.5 &amp;#180; 0.9--1.7(--2.4) mm, margins folded. Inflorescences: staminate spathes subglobose to ovoid, 2.2--4 mm; peduncles abscissing in bud; pistillate spathes linear, 8.5--15 mm. Flowers unisexual; staminate flowers: stamens 9, pedicels briefly remaining attached following anthesis; inner 3 filaments connate proximally, forming column; anthers 1--1.4 mm; pollen in tetrads; pistillate flowers: styles mostly 1.2--2 mm. Seeds fusiform, 4--4.6 mm, base with long hairs. 2n = 48 (Britain).</description>
